18:36.748 --> 18:39.912
Verse 9, but now you have rejected and humbled us.

18:40.893 --> 18:42.836
You no longer go out with our armies.

18:42.896 --> 18:46.341
You made us retreat before the enemy and our adversaries have plundered us.

18:47.442 --> 18:51.108
You gave us up to be devoured like sheep and have scattered us among the nations.

18:51.708 --> 18:55.794
You sold your people for a pittance gaining nothing from their sale.

18:56.290 --> 19:01.516
You have made us a reproach to our neighbors, the scorn and derision of those around us.

19:02.317 --> 19:04.659
You have made us a byword among the nations.

19:05.080 --> 19:07.022
The peoples shake their head at us.

19:08.584 --> 19:12.688
And at its personal, I live in disgrace all day long.

19:12.708 --> 19:20.817
And my face is covered with shame at the taunts of those who reproach and revile me because of my enemy who has bent on revenge.

19:21.998 --> 19:25.362
All this came upon us, even though we had not forgotten you,

19:26.146 --> 19:27.929
We had not been false to your covenant.

19:28.670 --> 19:29.992
Our hearts had not turned back.

19:30.132 --> 19:35.039
Our feet had not strayed from your path, but you crushed us and made us haunt for jackals.

19:35.560 --> 19:37.402
You covered us over with deep darkness.

19:38.444 --> 19:46.656
If we had forgotten the name of our God or spread out our hands to a foreign God, would not God have discovered it since he knows the secret of the heart?

19:47.717 --> 19:50.221
Yet for your sake, we face death all day long.

19:51.162 --> 19:53.586
We are considered as sheep to be slaughtered.

19:54.850 --> 19:56.892
So he says, Awake, O Lord, why do you sleep?

19:57.633 --> 19:58.293
Browse yourself.

19:58.333 --> 19:59.635
Do not reject us forever.

19:59.675 --> 20:02.858
Why do you hide your face and forget our misery and oppression?

20:03.558 --> 20:05.220
We are brought down to the dust.

20:05.600 --> 20:07.282
Our bodies cling to the ground.

20:07.802 --> 20:08.943
Rise up and help us.

20:09.664 --> 20:11.526
Rescue us because of your unfailing love.

20:13.528 --> 20:13.748
Wow.

20:15.450 --> 20:17.111
See, this is not born out of cheap blame.

20:17.151 --> 20:24.178
This is born out of a deep sense that, God, you have always been faithful.

20:25.378 --> 20:26.039
But what happened?

20:28.062 --> 20:32.289
Prayers like this are not an attack on God's goodness as much as they are a cry for justice.

20:33.651 --> 20:39.039
Because he lament recognizes the problems and some of the promises.

20:39.580 --> 20:44.267
It says we are promised health, but yet sometimes sickness finds us.

20:45.128 --> 20:47.131
We are promised provision, but sometimes it doesn't come.

20:47.151 --> 20:50.516
We are promised protection, but sometimes we are not protected.

20:50.937 --> 20:54.322
We're promised strength beyond temptation, and yet sometimes we still fall

20:54.530 --> 20:56.172
into addictions.

20:57.834 --> 20:59.776
And see, lamented just speaking to God about this.

21:02.439 --> 21:03.000
He's being honest.

21:03.020 --> 21:03.981
God, here's what's going on.

21:04.001 --> 21:04.502
Here's where I'm at.

21:04.522 --> 21:05.403
Here's what I'm feeling over.

21:06.464 --> 21:09.047
Where are you God?

21:09.067 --> 21:11.029
And it's not out of a cheap, you know, where's my manager kind of thing?

21:11.049 --> 21:11.890
It's like, I know you are God.

21:11.930 --> 21:12.551
I know you're real.

21:14.834 --> 21:22.162
It's okay to mourn because blessed are those who mourn because they will be comforted.

21:23.778 --> 21:26.862
So be honest with God, and that takes faith to be honest with God.

21:28.044 --> 21:32.049
So ask yourself, am I able to be honest with God when I'm not seeing Him in my life?

21:34.031 --> 21:42.202
Sometimes the desire for optimal outcome or gods, miracle in our lives, is sometimes the only thing that we can see.

21:44.946 --> 21:51.314
If you think, well, no, this can happen, this can happen, this can happen, and we don't take time sometimes just to sit in and just be honest and be like, oh, but this is awful.

21:53.346 --> 21:54.608
God, hear my cry.

21:54.688 --> 21:55.829
Where are you, Lord?

21:55.849 --> 21:56.350
I need you.

21:59.033 --> 22:00.515
And watch how he meets you.

22:00.815 --> 22:02.658
Watch how you're comforted through that.

22:03.699 --> 22:04.640
He's with you in the victory.

22:04.680 --> 22:09.787
He'll be there with the victory, but also an ever-present help in times of trouble.

22:11.429 --> 22:12.710
So it's okay to cry.

22:12.911 --> 22:13.732
It's okay to hurt.

22:14.312 --> 22:15.374
It's okay to ask why.

22:16.495 --> 22:18.738
Just remember that it all comes from a place of faith.

22:20.866 --> 22:22.028
And if you're ever wondering, what do I do?

22:22.168 --> 22:23.369
What do I pray in that moment?

22:23.650 --> 22:24.371
Go to the Psalms.

22:24.691 --> 22:26.794
There are lots of Psalms like the one I just read.

22:27.135 --> 22:28.116
And just read through that.

22:30.579 --> 22:32.442
And just sort of join in with them as he's going through.

22:32.462 --> 22:33.563
Yes, I believe God can do everything.

22:33.583 --> 22:34.324
Yes, I can do everything.

22:34.344 --> 22:35.246
He can do this thing.

22:35.286 --> 22:37.509
I've seen him do miracles before, but where is he now?

22:37.529 --> 22:42.495
So you can be honest with God in that.

22:45.119 --> 22:50.226
And this is why it's a good thing to find people in your life who can get close to you.

22:50.562 --> 22:57.714
who you can be honest with and who can share in that with you, can be there for you in that pain.

22:59.397 --> 22:59.717
Amen?

23:00.960 --> 23:03.724
All right, man, ended on a downer note, but that's kind of where it went.

23:04.385 --> 23:05.988
It's kind of hard to bring it back from lament.

23:07.190 --> 23:08.933
So let's play one more praise song.

23:08.973 --> 23:10.275
Rejoice in the Lord or myself?

23:10.295 --> 23:10.456
No.

23:11.017 --> 23:12.138
All right, well, cool.

23:12.199 --> 23:15.584
Let's just close in prayer and then we will head back and get our soup.

23:15.965 --> 23:16.626
Lord God,

23:19.650 --> 23:23.514
I think a lot of us in here can relate with the psalmist there.

23:25.115 --> 23:26.116
Lord, we know you're real.

23:26.276 --> 23:27.918
We've seen you do miracles.

23:28.639 --> 23:30.200
God, I've seen you do miracles in my life.

23:32.182 --> 23:36.286
And then there's been times too, Lord, where it just seems like you're not there.

23:36.607 --> 23:37.568
The miracle doesn't come.

23:39.970 --> 23:41.832
The prayer for healing doesn't get answered.

23:44.354 --> 23:48.338
The Lord help us have faith enough to be honest with you.

23:48.418 --> 23:56.547
as we go through our struggles, knowing that you are always faithful, that you're an ever present help in times of trouble.

23:56.567 --> 24:10.261
So Lord, I pray right now if there's those out there that are mourning going through something God, I pray that you comfort them, as you said that you would, that your grace be there with them.

24:10.942 --> 24:15.026
Let them know that you are with them, even in the tough times.

24:17.218 --> 24:24.809
And Lord, with all that in mind, we know that while your kingdom is not here yet, we know that you are going to make all things new.

24:25.250 --> 24:28.455
You will wipe every tear, heal every sickness.

24:29.596 --> 24:33.462
And until that day, God, we continue to trust you and continue to follow you.

24:34.944 --> 24:38.089
With your saving grace, you pray in your name, amen.

24:38.109 --> 24:39.771
All right, you may be dismissed.

24:40.152 --> 24:41.554
Enjoy yourself some soup.

